                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/26647",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I'm unable to reproduce this. However, when _forward() is called, and the newly called action does not have a matching context, then the context view suffix from the original action is assumed -- which is incorrect behavior. As an example, if action A defines and detects an xml context, and then forwards to action B, which defines only a json context but does not detect it, the view suffix xml.phtml will be re-used. More appropriate is to use the original view suffix (phtml) -- or, in the action method, determine if a valid context was found.\n\nI will fix the code so that the original view suffix is returned.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-11-24T12:40:34.000+0000",
